title: Fast motion clip from Nohyal
description: Fast motion vs. Timelapse? "Fast Motion" video is typically shot at a normal frame rate, and then sped up afterwards. "Timelapse" uses a longer interval between frames, and then plays back at a normal frame rate. It's the difference between hours or days sped into seconds vs minutes sped into seconds.
